<doc id="620472" wikidata="Q2128998" url="?curid=620472" title="Rakatak">
<text>The Rakatak is a percussion instrument that originates from Ghana. The rakatak is made of several calabash gourd shells attached to a long, narrow wooden shaft joined to the longer main wooden handle at a 90-degree angle. Rakataks are often used in traditional African ... music.

