<doc id="620503" wikidata="Q2597329" url="?curid=620503" title="Rakovskovo">
<text>Rakovskovo () is a small village located in southeast Bulgaria, situated in Obshtina Nessebar, in the Burgas region. It is made up of small farms and summer villas. The village lies in the foothills of the Balkan Mountains, and is within a 15-minute drive to the Black Sea beach town of Obzor. As of 2024, the population of Rakovskovo is 79. The village is named after Georgi Sava Rakovski, a Bulgarian revolutionary and nationalist.

